title: 2 Buffalo Police officers injured in rollover accident
text:
The accident happened at Tonawanda Street and Hertel Avenue just before 1:30 a.m. Wednesday.

BUFFALO, N.Y. — Two Buffalo Police officers were injured following an early morning accident.

The accident happened at Tonawanda Street and Hertel Avenue just before 1:30 a.m. Wednesday.

Investigators say the two officers were responding to a call with their lights and sirens on when their patrol vehicle was struck by another vehicle causing the police vehicle to rollover.

The two officers were taken to ECMC and treated for minor injuries. It's unknown if anyone else involved in the accident was hurt.
